Player_Romus

"I was just thinking how much territory we've lost throughout the last centuries."

Pabel Adria

"I will leave you to it, Your Majesty. I hope it's a very productive meeting."

Narrator

Duke Reinhart strode into the hall, glancing around at the paintings and tapestries on the walls.

Player_Romus

"Welcome to Rizia, Your Grace."

Axel Reinhart

"Quite fascinating, really."

Player_Romus

"I'm hoping to see its direct results on the economy."

Player_Romus

"That's great news. Rizia looks forward to receiving Palesian gas."

Axel Reinhart

"Actually... I believe Mr. Alvarez wanted to talk to you about that."

Player_Romus

"And what might that be, Your Grace?"

Axel Reinhart

"I'm not hinting at anything yet. I just want to hear what the King of Rizia thinks."

Axel Reinhart

"I like how you think."

Axel Reinhart

"I'm just wondering whether Rizia is ready to take this whole *good neighbor* thing to the next level."

Axel Reinhart

"I'd like to believe the resolution we reached, and the crises we've shepherded through together were more than just handshakes or numbers."

Player_Romus

"Of course. We share the same intentions."

Player_Romus

"I am ready to go further with Pales, Your Grace."

Axel Reinhart

"Great. I like how you think."

Axel Reinhart

"I understand."

Axel Reinhart

"Then perhaps it's time we talk about that."

Axel Reinhart

"If everything goes to plan, it will be ready at the end of the year."

Player_Romus

"Let's talk details."

Player_Romus

"You'd better offer us the best discount you can give."

Narrator

There was a brief silence, his expression thoughtful. He smiled.

Axel Reinhart

"Look, Your Majesty..."

Player_Romus

"Exactly. I already had some ideas I want to discuss with you myself."

Axel Reinhart

"Quite amazing and going pretty fast, really."

Axel Reinhart

"...I believe I gave you all the news I've had for you already for the time being."

Axel Reinhart

"...Perhaps it's time to talk about our energy deal."

Player_Romus

"I do. I have an offer for you."

Player_Romus

"I don't really see a need to discuss anything. We've cooperated enough already."

Axel Reinhart

"I'm excited to hear that."

Axel Reinhart

"I still believe there's a lot more we can do together."

Player_Romus

"I thought it was Lespia who's really in control."

Player_Romus

"I was expecting a discount not a damn scam."

Player_Romus

"12 Arcasian Liras? That's more expensive than every other source around the region."

Player_Romus

"That seems agreeable."

Player_Romus

"This is a direct consequence of your willingness to give control of your country to Lespia, Your Grace. Fearing Rizia, you dealt with the devil instead."

Player_Romus

"It is a discussion we must have."

Narrator

He sighed.

Axel Reinhart

"And now that Rizia has gained our trust, it might be a possibility to reconsider certain agreements with Lespia -- provided that there is an alternative offer from our new partners."

Axel Reinhart

"What of GRACE, Your Majesty?"

Axel Reinhart

"I see."

Axel Reinhart

"I'd like to believe so. Apart from the incident we shall not speak of, your kingdom's actions have been more than reconciliatory."

Axel Reinhart

"However, I also believe Rizia and Pales are natural partners. Our countries are politically and culturally the closest in Southern Merkopa -- maybe even the whole world."

Narrator

He paused and gave me an intense stare, as if he was expecting me to cut in with an offer.

Player_Romus_Italic

I waited for him to speak.

Axel Reinhart

"Drifting away from Lespia would necessitate strong allies -- with common goals."

Narrator

He sighed.

Axel Reinhart

"I've already told you before about what I think of them. But Lespia provides us with protection, technology and the know-how about kickstarting our own energy industries."

Player_Romus

"Then please let me offer you an alternative."

Axel Reinhart

"Unfortunately for the time being, you have to directly deal with Lespia for the energy prices."

Axel Reinhart

"I'm all ears."

Player_Romus

"What? Do you want me to censor history just because our guest finds it offensive?"

Player_Romus

"Mr. Alvarez sent you to do his bidding and you agreed, did you not?"

Player_Romus

"You deserve nothing, Axel."

Player_Romus

"You can still let go of your deal with them. You don't need to rely on Lespia any longer."

Narrator

His face soured.

Axel Reinhart

"Well... Before I get there, I have to relay you some news."

Narrator

He looked like he was going to say something but then stopped himself.

Axel Reinhart

"I've already told you before about what I think of them. But Lespia provides us with protection, technology and the know-how about kickstarting our own energy industries."

Player_Romus

"What do you have in mind?"

Axel Reinhart

"And now that Rizia gained our trust, it might be a possibility to reconsider certain agreements with Lespia -- provided that there is an alternative offer from our new partners."

Axel Reinhart

"Well... Then let me relay you the news I was here for."

Player_Romus

"I am not, Your Grace. I believe we've cooperated enough already."

Narrator

He sighed.

Player_Romus

"I have nothing left to offer you."

Narrator

He stood up and shook my hand.

Axel Reinhart

"Rizia is a key member. Have you considered extending an invitation our way?"

Player_Romus

"I do not support the membership of Pales into GRACE."

Player_Romus

"I want to pursue an alliance with Pales -- but I don't believe GRACE is the right way to do this, Your Grace. We need a regional alliance, not a reliance on Rumburg."

Axel Reinhart

"Really? That's incredible news!"

Axel Reinhart

"Interesting perspective."

Player_Romus

"I don't think Pales belongs in GRACE."

Axel Reinhart

"Oh, please, Your Majesty. You're saying that because you don't want us to be part of it."

Player_Romus

"Yes. We will bring it up to the members and initiate your application."

Player_Romus

"Yes. But I expect you to stop all of your partnerships with Lespia."

Axel Reinhart

"Thank you, Your Majesty."

Player_Romus

"It's time we stand together. I'm offering you a military alliance. Rizia can give you the protection you require, you don't need Lespia anymore."

Player_Romus

"I envision a grander alliance that encompasses our neighbors in Southern Merkopa. We have to protect this region from the encroaching world powers. If you and I work together, we can achieve this."

Player_Romus

"It's time we stand together. I'm offering you a military alliance. Rizia can give you the protection you require. You won't need Lespia anymore."

Player_Romus

"I envision a grander alliance that encompasses our neighbors in Southern Merkopa. We have to protect this region from encroaching world powers. If you and I work together, we can achieve this."

Axel Reinhart

"An intriguing proposal."

Axel Reinhart

"What would this new alliance look like?"

Axel Reinhart

"I thought you wanted to sway us away from Lespia. This could have been a way to offer us protection."

Player_Romus

"I don't. It no longer is in the best interest of the nation."

Axel Reinhart

"A military alliance, you say?"

Axel Reinhart

"This is a serious offer."

Axel Reinhart

"That is a serious proposal, Your Majesty."

Player_Romus

"I will be honest, Your Grace. I still wish to see Rizia and Pales reunited. And I believe it is possible with a bond of marriage."

Axel Reinhart

"The thought of a Rizia-Pales reunion has certainly crossed my mind. And of course, a marriage between myself and Princess Vina would be the natural way to accomplish that."

Narrator

He looked down and stroked his chin.

Axel Reinhart

"So you have a better suggestion?"

Axel Reinhart

"Then we must continue our partnership with Lespia. I'm sure you understand."

Axel Reinhart

"Thank you, Your Majesty."

Axel Reinhart

"One that I would gladly accept!"

Player_Romus

"That's not all. I envision a grander alliance that encompasses our neighbors in Southern Merkopa. We have to protect this region from the encroaching world powers. Now as allies, we can build this together."

Player_Romus

"Finally! May our alliance last long."

Axel Reinhart

"We will, Your Majesty, but we cannot cut everything in an instant. We have to respect our current agreements."

Player_Romus

"I think we've already discussed everything we possibly can."

Axel Reinhart

"There's one more thing. Don't you think Rizia and Pales deserve a more... intimate connection?"

Player_Romus

"Of course not! Relax, Axel. I will send your application."

Player_Romus

"Yes, Your Grace. It's time Pales offers something to Rizia."

Axel Reinhart

"Fine, Your Majesty. But I can only offer you money."

Axel Reinhart

"You're still not seeing Pales as an equal partner, Your Majesty."

Axel Reinhart

"Right."

Axel Reinhart

"Until next time."

Axel Reinhart

"So, was there anything else you'd like to discuss?"

Axel Reinhart

"Great. Then we can call it for today."

Player_Romus

"No, Your Grace, thank you."

Player_Romus

"Homosexuality is a crime in this kingdom."

Player_Romus

"Absolutely not."

Narrator

He laughed.

Narrator

He laughed.

Axel Reinhart

"I have admired Princess Vina for some time now."

Player_Romus

"Out of the question."

Player_Romus

"Marrying the heir to the throne? That's quite a leap from energy agreements."

Axel Reinhart

"This union would not only be a powerful symbol of reconciliation between our families, but a merging of our countries' destinies."

Axel Reinhart

"I'm sure we can find solutions to any problem you had in mind. Just think about it."

Player_Romus

"I will not give the Rizian throne to a Valgish family."

Player_Romus

"And what name will that be? Torhart? I'm open to compromise."

Axel Reinhart

"Of course, Your Majesty."

Player_Romus

"What is there to think about? You and my daughter shall be wed, and our kingdoms shall unite as one."

Player_Romus

"Forget about it, Duke Reinhart. I can already tell you my daughter isn't interested."

Axel Reinhart

"Thank you."

Player_Romus

"Imagine this. Morella, Derdia, Wehlen, Pales and Rizia together -- we could stand against both the CSP and the ATO."

Player_Romus

"This is precisely why we have to work with them. They are not part of the CSP yet and we need them with us."

Player_Romus

"Leave that to me."

Player_Romus

"As long as it's not a clear no, that's enough."

Player_Romus

"I understand."

Axel Reinhart

"I'm all ears."

Player_Romus

"I'm not willing to take that risk right now."

Player_Romus

"Absolutely not."

Axel Reinhart

"Amazing!"

Axel Reinhart

"Fine. Fair enough."

Player_Romus

"Good to know."

Player_Romus

"That's good enough for me."

Axel Reinhart

"I understand. Thank you, Your Majesty."

Axel Reinhart

"I am open to re-discussing our agricultural imports from Rizia. If you can provide us our demands, we'll let go of our other partners and I'll agree to the Rizian prices."

Player_Romus

"See you soon."

Axel Reinhart

"I know such things are now condoned in your kingdom, Your Majesty, but you're not really my type."

Axel Reinhart

"Flattering, Your Majesty. But you're not really my type."

Axel Reinhart

"Don't worry, Your Majesty. I wasn't referring to you."

Player_Romus

"My daughter is already spoken for, Your Grace."

Axel Reinhart

"Interesting. I don't see a ring on her finger."

Axel Reinhart

"I've made a lot of proposals, Your Majesty. But never serious ones. Until now."

Player_Romus

"I do not wish to discuss this further without my daughter's full consent. This is her decision to make, not mine."

Axel Reinhart

"Absolutely. But I've seen Her Highness' brilliant mind in action. She won't refuse the chance to make history."

Axel Reinhart

"That goes without saying."

Narrator

He shrugged.

Player_Romus

"Let's not go down this path, Your Grace. There are more modern ways of allying our nations."

Player_Romus

"I do have one other offer I'd like to extend your way."
